==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alleviation
<hw>Al*le`vi*a"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>alleviatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of alleviating; a
lightening of weight or severity; mitigation; relief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 41 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which mitigates, or makes more
tolerable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have not wanted such <qex>alleviations</qex> of life as
friendship could supply.</q> <rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alleviative</ent>⟦br⟧
